description: Enforce LrTasks.pcall over raw pcall
alwaysApply: true
---

# Use `LrTasks.pcall`, never raw `pcall`

- Do not introduce calls to Lua `pcall(...)`.
- Use `LrTasks.pcall(...)` for protected calls in this project.
- If touching older code, migrate raw `pcall` usages to `LrTasks.pcall`.

Example:

```lua
-- Bad
local ok, result = pcall(doWork)

-- Good
local ok, result = LrTasks.pcall(doWork)
```
